RAZER KRAKEN V4 PRO

FULL IMMERSION. FULL CONTROL.

Experience next-gen immersion with the Razer Kraken V4 Pro—a wireless RGB headset powered by Razer Sensa HD Haptics. Equipped with a dedicated OLED Control Hub for maximum command at your fingertips, send your gaming into overdrive with the ultimate battlestation headset that can do it all.

This is a carousel. Use Next and Previous buttons to navigate, or jump to a slide using the slide dots.

OLED CONTROL HUB

Full Customizability and Multi-Platform Connectivity

Centralize the control of your battlestation with one powerful device featuring over 20 customization options. Personalize your experience by adjusting audio, haptics, power-saving, and home screen settings easily via an ergonomically angled interface.

QUICK ACCESS MODES

Instantly adjust to your liking with an intuitive clickable control knob.

HOME SCREEN

Customize the OLED display to show a wide range of visuals and text.

Tap the 'MODE' button on the OLED Control Hub to cycle through nine essential settings.

  • Adjust the level of your system volume.

  • Select between 4 audio EQ profiles: Game, Movie, Music, and Custom.

  • Select between 4 haptic profiles: Controlled, Balanced, Dynamic, and Custom.

  • Adjust the strength of haptic feedback.

  • Switch between multiple audio input sources based on devices connected.

  • Set the level of your mic monitoring sidetone.

  • Find the perfect mix between game and chat audio.

  • Adjust the level of Razer Chroma RGB lighting.

  • Adjust the level of OLED display brightness.

  • Display preset GIF animation or upload your own via Razer Synapse.

  • Obtain vital information of your system at a glance.

  • Show your current headset status and settings.

  • Display preset static image or upload your own via Razer Synapse.

  • Obtain useful information on the current track with an interactive audio visualizer.

  • Customize any text or quote that continuously scrolls across the display.

RAZER SENSA™
HD HAPTICS

Next-Gen Haptic Feedback

Feel your games like never before with the next leap in haptic technology. Experience layered and realistic haptic feedback that mirrors the intensity, direction, and duration of in-game audio.

Learn More >

HAPTIC SOURCE

Audio-to-Haptics

Sensa HD Haptics supports real-time audio-to-haptics conversion. Designed to work with all forms of audio content, enjoy your favorite games, movies and music with next-level immersion. Enhance your enjoyment even further with an ever-growing list of Sensa-tuned game profiles created to meet your specific preference.

View All Sensa-Tuned Game Profiles >

Sensa Game Integration

Overhaul your gaming sessions and reach new heights of immersion through specially tuned haptic effects created in partnership with game developers. Experience in-game events such as cutscenes and character actions through countless custom, high-definition haptic effects–blurring the lines between game and reality.

4 MODES OF CONNECTIVITY

Razer™ HyperSpeed Wireless | Bluetooth | USB Wired | 3.5 mm

Whether you’re on PC, PlayStation, Nintendo Switch, or on your mobile device, enjoy full audio immersion no matter the scenario with Razer’s first gaming headset to offer 4 modes of connectivity. Go wireless with ultra-fast 2.4 GHz, Bluetooth connectivity, or stay plugged in for non-stop gaming via USB. Connect up to 3 systems or devices at the same time to the OLED Control Hub and switch between audio sources with seamless convenience.

SIMULTANEOUS 2.4GHz & BLUETOOTH AUDIO

Listen in to two audio connections simultaneously when using Razer HyperSpeed wireless alongside a Bluetooth device. Stay on comms with your squad at all times via Discord on mobile whilst playing your favorite games on PC/Console.

RETRACTABLE RAZER™ HYPERCLEAR SUPER WIDEBAND MIC

High-Definition, Pro-Level Voice Quality

Featuring technology derived from our award-winning Razer BlackShark V2 Pro, this next-gen retractable mic captures an incredible amount of detail in your voice by covering a wider frequency range of sound, so that everything you say sounds clear, rich, and natural.

FLUSHED RETRACTABLE DESIGN

Seamless Ease-of-Use

Simply pull out the mic and be ready to go. Get it into the perfect position thanks to a flexible gooseneck wire, and easily tuck it back into the earcup when not in use. Additionally, easily view your mic status with a conveniently-located mic mute indicator.

RAZER™ TRIFORCE BIO-CELLULOSE 40 MM DRIVERS

Natural, High-End Sound

Our upgraded Razer TriForce Driver design utilizes an ultra-thin bio-cellulose diaphragm, improving the soundstage and reducing distortion for distinct clarity and deep bass reproduction. Enjoy the rich environmental sounds of your in-game world with clear distinction between voices and audio cues.

FAQS

  • What’s new with the Razer Kraken V4 Pro?

    The Razer Kraken V4 Pro features Sensa HD Haptics and an all-new OLED Control Hub. It is Razer’s first headset to offer 4 connectivity options: 2.4 GHz wireless, Bluetooth, USB wired, and 3.5 mm. Design changes include a swivel mechanism, a flushed & retractable Razer HyperClear Super Wideband Mic, and 9-zone earcup lighting powered by Razer Chroma RGB.

  • What connectivity options are available on the Razer Kraken V4 Pro?

    The headset offers 4 modes of connectivity; 2.4GHz wireless & 3.5mm via the OLED Control Hub, Bluetooth mode supported by Razer SmartSwitch Dual Wireless, and USB-wired via the provided USB cables. It also offers simultaneous 2.4GHz & BT audio.

  • Should I be using Razer HyperSpeed Wireless (2.4GHz) or Bluetooth for PC gaming?

    Razer HyperSpeed Wireless (2.4GHz) is optimal for gaming with its ultra-low latency of 15 ms and more stable connectivity, while Bluetooth offers mobile convenience on the go without the need for an additional wireless dongle.

  • Can I customize the home screen on the OLED Control Hub?

    Yes, select your home screen of choice via the OLED Control Hub menu, which offers various options of animation, images, emotes, text banners, and more. On top of that, you can upload custom gifs, images, and text to be downloaded on-board the Hub itself.

  • How do I activate THX Spatial Audio?

    THX Spatial Audio comes automatically with the Razer Kraken V4 Pro and is integrated within Razer Synapse. Download Razer Synapse here.

  • What audio EQ profile should I be using?

    For the best audio experience, Razer recommends using the ‘Game’ EQ for competitive shooter games, ‘Movie’ EQ for MOBAs, RPGs or watching movies, and ‘Music’ EQ for all forms of music content. A fourth ‘Custom’ EQ is also available. All audio EQ profiles can be personalized via the Razer Synapse app to strike that perfect audio balance.

  • Do I have to activate Razer Sensa HD Haptics?

    Razer Sensa HD Haptics works right out of the box without any additional activation or installation needed. Additionally, the Razer Chroma app on Synapse 4 will unlock further haptics customization with Sensa HD Haptics.

  • Are there different audio-to-haptic profiles I can choose from?

    Yes, there are 4 different profiles available. ‘Controlled’ is a bass-focused profile with a subwoofer-like response, designed to enhance bass presence with physical sensations. ‘Balanced’ is optimized to provide a smooth response for mild scenes and strong responses for high-intensity events. ‘Dynamic’ is a reactive profile maximizing immersion and spatial awareness, allowing action-packed events to feel more vivid and present. ‘Custom’ allows you to pick from any of the previous profiles and personalize it further by setting your own frequency ranges and haptic gain.

  • How do I use simultaneous audio on the Razer Kraken V4 Pro?

    Once you have paired the headset with your Bluetooth device, double-tap the Multi-function button (MFB) on the headset to cycle through connection modes and enter simultaneous audio connection. You will now be able to listen in on both 2.4 GHz and Bluetooth audio streams at the same time.

  • What can I control with the on-earcup Multi-function button (MFB) & Sensa button?

    Sensa button – Single tap to select haptics intensity (Low, Med, High, Off), Double tap to select audio-to-haptic profile (Controlled, Balanced, Dynamic, Custom)

    MFB – Press and hold for 7 sec to enter Bluetooth pairing mode, Single tap to select audio EQ profile (Game, Movie, Music, Custom), Double tap to select wireless mode (HyperSpeed Wireless, Bluetooth, Simultaneous Audio)

  • How long does it take to charge the Razer Kraken V4 Pro?

    A full charge of 50 hours of play time will take around 4 hours, while 15 minutes of charge will yield approximately 5 hours of play time.

  • Why doesn’t the Razer Kraken V4 Pro appear on Synapse 3?

    The headset is only supported on Razer Synapse 4 for its full suite of features and customization. Download Razer Synapse here.
